remarks.format:
## Remarks

`SKFourByteTag` represents an OpenType/TrueType four-character tag encoded as a
32-bit unsigned integer. The four ASCII characters are packed as
`(c1 << 24) | (c2 << 16) | (c3 << 8) | c4`. Common examples are `'wght'` for the
weight variation axis and `'wdth'` for width.

`SKFourByteTag` is a value type and does not require disposal. It converts implicitly
to and from `uint`, and can be constructed from a string via <xref:SkiaSharp.SKFourByteTag.Parse(System.String)>.

## Examples

```csharp
// Construct from individual characters
var weightTag = new SKFourByteTag('w', 'g', 'h', 't');

// Construct from a string
var widthTag = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wdth");

// Use as variation axis identifier
var coord = new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate
{
    Axis = weightTag,
    Value = 700f,
};
```
